   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>SUPPLEMENTARY MESSAGES REGARDING</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>CERTAIN MATTERS IN THE CHURCH</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>THAT REQUIRE OUR ATTENTION THE OUTLINE There being no organizational unification among the churches: The examples in the Bible.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Two dangers.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Not having organizational unification: Not being unified in the move of the work.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Not being unified in finance.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Not having a central church or person.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The proper attitude: Not being individualistic or loose.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Needing to seek confirmation.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Some matters related to full-time service: Serving full time being a matter of commission: Everyone needing to serve.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Serving full time being based on the Lord s commission.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Needing to learn how to do things.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Giving all the brothers and sisters an opportunity to serve.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>The question of financial support.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Character and disposition.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Knowing the spiritual aspect of the church: The church being in resurrection: The experience of resurrection.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>The way to experience resurrection.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The church being spiritual: Resurrection and the Holy Spirit being inseparable.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>The church existing only in the Holy Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>The church being heavenly: The church being heavenly according to its nature.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>Heaven being related to the authority of God.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>To be heavenly being to submit to the authority of God.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>The heavenly condition of the church.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Receiving people in the churches: An explanation of the fact and the principle.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>Two aspects of salvation believing and being baptized.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>What man obtains through believing.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>Baptism being based upon the faith one already has.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>Needing to touch a person s inner feeling when receiving him.</S>
